description: Primes that contain digits 8 and 9 only.
links: Vincenzo Librandi, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000
Index to entries about primes with digits in a given set
mathematica: Select[Prime[Range[80000]], Min[IntegerDigits[ # ]]==8&] - _Zak Seidov_, May 07 2005Flatten[Table[Select[FromDigits/@Tuples[{8,9},n],PrimeQ],{n,8}]] (* _Vincenzo Librandi_, Jul 27 2012 *)
